title: Pregnant Amy Childs admits X Factor rapper Honey G has "put her off" the name Honey for her baby girl
text:
Pregnant Amy Childs admits X Factor rapper Honey G has "put her off" the name Honey for her baby girl Share Amy isn't keen on the baby name Honey Share Get   
Pregnant Amy Childs has admitted X Factor rapper Honey G has put her off naming her daughter Honey. 
The former TOWIE star confirmed this week that she’s expecting a baby girl with boyfriend Bradley Wright which means, of course, she’s already got her thinking cap on when it comes to the perfect baby name - or the ones she wants to avoid. 
“One of my girls said I should call her Honey, but if I’m honest, Honey G has put me off!” laughed Amy. “Plus, I call everyone honey so it would be confusing. Ha! I won’t be giving her a middle name, though. Amy is expecting a baby girl (Photo: Rex Features) Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now Share this video Watch Next 
"Her surname will be Childs Wright, so she’ll already have three names and that’s enough,” she wrote in her New magazine column. 
Amy, 26, admitted she and Brad have been thinking about possible baby names but haven’t settled on any favourites just yet, although they have a shortlist. 
“Even though we found out what we were having early on, we still haven’t come up with a name. We have a list of five - Brad chose two and I chose the rest - but we’re going to wait until she’s here before we decided. 
“Brad likes traditional names but I’m not too sure. I’m not saying mine are out there, but maybe a bit different. I really liked India at first, but I’ve gone off that now.” 
The reality TV personality first revealed the sex of her baby in an interview with OK magazine, admitting she was stunned as she'd believed it would be a boy. 
"I think I'm still in shock. Instinct told me it would be a boy. A psychic told me it was going to be a boy and lots of people I knew thought the same. 
"I even ordered a boy Moncler baby bag because I was so convinced. But it's a girl!". 
Brentwood-born Amy was told the child's gender after thirteen weeks, but added that she was happy to have a tot of either gender - as long as they were healthy. 
"I don't mind as long as it's a healthy baby," she added. "I've wanted a baby for so long." 
Her revelation came shortly after she shared an image of the scan via Instagram. The mother-to-be shared a snapshot of her baby with her 390,000 followers on the photo-sharing app. 
The high-tech image shows the reality star's child in striking detail, with the baby's features clearly defined and pronounced. 
Seemingly lost for words at seeing her child's face, the emotional star simply captioned the snap: "Words can't describe how much I love you." Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now
